sentences.sentence: Twenty-two-year-old Skeeter has just returned home after graduating from Ole Miss.
sentences.translation: 22岁的 Skeeter 刚从密西西比大学毕业后回到家乡。

sentences.sentence: Pike, who starred in An Education last year, was the first choice to play Skeeter, but she said no to playing the nosy journalist.
sentences.translation: 去年主演了《成长教育》的派克才是扮演斯基特的首要人选，但她拒绝了扮演一个八卦记者。

sentences.sentence: Typically, these symptoms occur within minutes after a mosquito bite, compared to Skeeter Syndrome, which may take hours to days to occur.
sentences.translation: 通常，这些症状在蚊子叮咬后几分钟内发作，而相比之下，史基特症候群常在被叮咬几小时或几天后发生。
